Enable or disable lighting. By default lighting is disabled.

### syntax

~~~ python
lighting(enable)
~~~

### parameters

enable | `True` or `False`


### examples

#### draw a solid sphere 


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "lighting", "draw-a-solid-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(True)
   material(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0, style="solid")
~~~

#### draw a wireframe sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "lighting", "draw-a-wireframe-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)
   color(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0)
~~~
